16 2021-03-30 pulmonary congestion 16 year old was vaccinated with Moderna on 3/11/21. Error was found on 3/26/21 by staff reviewing r... Read more
Close
16 year old was vaccinated with Moderna on 3/11/21. Error was found on 3/26/21 by staff reviewing registration list for upcoming covid vaccine clinics. Spoke with patient and her mother on 3/30/21 to report what happened. Patient reported feeling very tired starting on the evening of 3/11/21 and continued until 3/12/21 around bedtime. Also had chills that started on 3/11/21 in the evening and lasted until 5pm on 3/12/21. Denies any other symptoms or problems.
17 2021-03-03 shortness of breath Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes ... Read more
Close
Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes to 1 hour after receiving her second Moderna vaccination on 2/24/21. She reported that she was told by her employer that the symptoms were due to the Moderna vaccine. She reportedly developed fever and some throat discomfort as well. Symptoms became persistent and disrupted sleep and was unable to work. She sought medical attention in the ER for persistent symptoms on 2/26/21. Extensive workup was essentially normal. She received Zofran, Decadron, IVFs, and Albuterol inhaler while in the ER. She reported improvement in her chest tightness and SOB after Albuterol. She was discharged home with instructions to f/u with her PCP in a couple of days for recheck.

She states that she does not have any shortness of breath currently but reports a sensation of shortness of breath. She states that she has had a headache for "weeks" she states that this headache has been unrelieved with medication including ibuprofen and acetaminophen as well as allergy medication that she has taken 2 doses of.

18 2021-01-13 shortness of breath, very rapid breathing Patient was screened and identified allergy to PCN. Covid Vaccine administered without incident. Nu... Read more
Close
Patient was screened and identified allergy to PCN. Covid Vaccine administered without incident. Nurse did insist client stay in area for 30 minutes due to history of PCN allergy. After about 10 minutes, client returned with complaint of itching, flushing in face and hyperventilating. LPH assisted and laid patient down and elevated her legs. Pulse was 200 and breathing difficulties increased. EPI 0.5 given IM in thigh by nurse. Patient felt significantly better after one dose of EPI and breathing was almost back to normal. Patient transported by EMS.

18 2021-01-14 wheezing I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or ... Read more
Close
I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or an hour after. About 2 hours later (at 2:00 pm), I developed some hives around my neck, and the part of my arm near the injection site started to become more and more sore. I applied Benadryl to the hives and they went away. However, my left arm hurt to touch or move, much worse than any vaccine I've had before (flu, HPV). That night, I had trouble sleeping because the discomfort because of the sore left arm. I also could not sleep because of chest tightness and pressure, which worsened when lying down, but that pressure did not progress to the point of wheezing (I have asthma). Sleeping on my back was the only option because sleeping on either side was painful, which worsened the chest pressure. When I woke up, my fingers felt stiff and I had joint pain in both hands, more so in my left hand. Throughout this, I did not see any redness on my arm. This day it was agonizing to move my left arm. I could pick things up, but raising it above my the height of my waist or twisting it behind my back to get on my backpack was near impossible and was avoided. The chest pressure went away. The second night, I still had trouble sleeping, but the pain was much better, although I still could not sleep on my side. When I woke up, I had no more joint pain. That day, although the left arm was still sore, I could move it pretty well. If I made too strong of a movement, it felt like the injection site would tense up, the pain would slowly ramp up, and then diminish. That afternoon, at 4:30, I was able to play tennis with minimal soreness, and that night, I was able to sleep on my side. The following day, I had a cough, but that might have been because I didn't dress for the weather, and experiences close to zero soreness.

Patient presented with "pressure on the throat, difficulty swallowing". Airway patent and lungs clear on initial observation in lower lobes with developed slight wheeze in upper airway on arrival to hospital 30 mins later. Patient received Albuterol 2.5mg/3cc saline nebulizer treatment during transport.

Around 3:45 PM patient developed sudden cough, congestion, and shortness of breath. Received first COVID shot on 3/19/21. On 3/20/21 presenting to ER with weakness, achiness, fever, shortness of breath after having coronavirus vaccination yesterday. Patient is sure she had coronavirus back in November. Received the vaccination yesterday about 11 am. Within a couple hours she developed severe myalgias, low-grade fever. Reports she feels a little short of breath from a myalgias. No history of DVT or PE, urinary complaints. Patient has syncopal episode while in triage. No seizure activity. Felt lightheaded with standing. Clinical Impression: 1. Syncope 2. Vaccination reaction, initial encounter Presentation consistent with orthostatic, vasovagal episode from recent vaccination. Patient coronavirus previously stimulating a stronger immune response. doubt infection, PE, worrisome arrthymia. Advised against second vaccination. return if any problems, worsening

Difficulty swallowing; Shortness of breath; Big rash; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 18-year old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced events shortness of breath, difficulty breathing, tightness on the throat, difficulty swallowing, big rash in forehead and under her eyes. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant medications reported were birth control pill for drug use for unknown indication. On 9 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the events the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: unknown) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 9 Mar 2021, the patient experienced the event shortness of breath, difficulty breathing, tightness on the throat, difficulty swallowing, big rash in forehead and under her eyes. Treatment details included went to the emergency room (ER), epinephrine, diphenhydramine, and dexamethasone.. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of event, shortness of breath, difficulty breathing, tightness on the throat, difficulty swallowing, big rash in forehead and under her eyes was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Right eye twinching; lightheadedness; rash on hands; Nausea; DOB; This case was received via an unknown source (no reference has been entered for a health authority or license partner) on 10-Feb-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 11-Feb-2021. This spontaneous case was reported by a nurse (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of BLEPHAROSPASM (Right eye twinching), DIZZINESS (lightheadedness), RASH (rash on hands), NAUSEA (Nausea) and DYSPNOEA (DOB) in an 18-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 037K20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. Concurrent medical conditions included Penicillin allergy since January 2021. On 29-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 29-Jan-2021, the patient experienced BLEPHAROSPASM (Right eye twinching) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), DIZZINESS (lightheadedness) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), RASH (rash on hands) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), NAUSEA (Nausea) (seriousness criterion hospitalization) and DYSPNOEA (DOB) (seriousness criterion hospitalization). At the time of the report, BLEPHAROSPASM (Right eye twinching), DIZZINESS (lightheadedness), RASH (rash on hands), NAUSEA (Nausea) and DYSPNOEA (DOB) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. Treatment for the events include 0.5ml Epinephrine on the left thigh This case concerns an 18 Y/O F hospitalized with serious unexpected events of blepharospasm, dizziness, rash, nausea, dyspnea. Event outcomes unknown. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Reporter did not allow further contact; Sender's Comments: This case concerns an 18 Y/O F hospitalized with serious unexpected events of blepharospasm, dizziness, rash, nausea, dyspnea. Event outcomes unknown. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

18 2021-04-19 shortness of breath The 12:20 pm appointment today (4/20/21) had an adverse reaction to the IMZ. Patient was done receiv... Read more
Close
The 12:20 pm appointment today (4/20/21) had an adverse reaction to the IMZ. Patient was done receiving the vaccine at about 12:30 pm and I stated she would have to wait until 12:45 pm. Around 12:38 pm I noticed she looked a little pale and went to her side to check on her. The patient stated she was feeling light-headed, dizzy, nauseous, and had trouble with her vision. I had the patient lay down and elevate her feet. The technician also grabbed an ice pack to place behind her neck. Asked if she would like water. The patient then stated she was having trouble breathing/short of breath and her ears were ringing. Once the patient stated issues with breathing 911 was called. A code white had been called and management was in the pharmacy. The 911 operator continued to ask questions about the patient's status and stated to not give any water or medications. I continued to assess the patient's symptoms. Her vision improved; however, she continued to feel light-headed, nauseous, and having trouble breathing. A member of EMS was in the store and came over to assess the patient. He had the patient sit up but she continued to have the same symptoms. He assessed her IMZ site. She was not feeling itchy and had not developed any hives. The ambulance arrived. EMS evaluated the patient and then took her out of the store on the stretcher.
18 2021-04-20 shortness of breath Within minutes (less than 5), patient began to faint and become extremely diaphoretic. Patient also ... Read more
Close
Within minutes (less than 5), patient began to faint and become extremely diaphoretic. Patient also lost control of her bladder and urinated while sitting in the chair. We immediately called 911 who stated not to move her our of the chair. Patient went in and out of consciousness several times (2-3) for short intervals (15-30 seconds). EMS arrived within 10 minutes of symptom onset and took her to the local hospital. While EMS was evaluating the patient in the pharmacy, she stated that she was beginning to have trouble breathing; but those symptoms quickly resolved without the administration of epinephrine. We received a phone call from the patient within 2 hours stating that she was being discharged from the hospital and was feeling much better.

Close
Febrile beginning at 1600, 100.5 degrees, peaking at 2100, 104degrees, accompanied with tightness in chest with mild difficulty breathing and extreme muscle weakness most notably in extremities, bilaterally. Needed assistance to stand and could not hold a pencil to write. Also numbness and tingling in hands and fingers. Face slightly swollen and red. 400 mg Ibuprofen was administered at 1530. Pushed fluids as soon as fever began. Cooling measures provided, cool shower, cold compress, change of clothes to light pajamas. We contacted our Insurance 24 hour Nurse line at approximately 2100 when symptoms peaked. The RN on staff instructed us to seek immediate medical care. We attempted to find an open Urgent Care unsuccessfully and tried to go to an ER but they were full. Fever began to come down around 2230, so we returned home. Continued with ibuprofen every six hours and cooling measures.

I could only breathe (faintly) to survive. If I took any deeper breaths, my back and chest would hurt even more. As time progressed, My right neck got stiff. Then right my jaw got stiff. Then the right side of my head got stiff. Eventually, the whole right side of my body was numb -- I could move it still but it was still numb and stiff. This happened simultaneously with the breathing issues. This entire time, my whole was tensing, it felt like I could feel my veins while it rushed blood. It was terrible. I thought I was going to die. I did not know which breath would be my last, because every breath got worse and worse. I went to sleep around 2AM and I would periodically wake up. When I'd wake, the pain still persisted. It never went away. Eventually I got up to go to work around 8AM, the right side of my body wasn't as numb and the breathing wasn't as bad, but you could still tell there was an issue. This issue persisted throughout the day. As of now, these issues are not as persistent, but at least once a day, I still feel the effect. It sucks. A nurse called me (working at the urgent care I gave information about) , on 05/03/2021 saying if I was going to see a primary doctor. I told her that I have an appointment with one on 05/10/2021. She said that though they called me on 05/02/2021 towards the end of the day and told me everything was fine, that they looked a little deeper and realized that the shape of my cells were weird and that when I go to my primary doctor, they'd be able to access my information. This is of a complete shock because the shape of my cells were never weird before. This happened as a result of the covid-19 vaccine. This is reaction must be put into the VAERS system.

A doctor in the clinic came over and even though it wasn't time for patient and her sister to leave (based on 15-minutes after receiving the vaccine) he initially suggested that they might be fine to go, but after patient told him of her symptoms and at my urging he decided to have her stay a little longer. I think it was at this time that he had someone check her pulse. I don't know what the pulse reading was. He stepped away and shortly afterwards patient started complaining that her throat felt strange and was making it hard to breathe. The doctor immediately came back over, found patient was having difficulty breathing and holding herself upright in the chair. I held her by the shoulders to keep her from falling while the doctor also steadied her and asked a worker in the room for an epi-pen. The worker didn't seem to react much to the request so he told her louder that he needed an epi-pen. She started searching her area and the doctor started yelling across the room to others that he needed an epi-pen. It seemed like others initially took the demand less urgently than they should, but eventually someone came with an epi-pen. By this time I don't think patient was very conscious, if at all. Sometime during this time the doctor also instructed someone to call 911. The doctor tried using the epi-pen but at first he had some kind of cap on it that prevented it from working. He removed the cap and not finding an easy way to have a sterilized injection site he injected the epi-pen through patient's jeans. Soon afterwards a cot was brought out and workers had me step aside as they took patient and put her on the cot. Patient seemed to gradually become more aware of her surroundings and it wasn't long before she appeared to me to be fully conscious once again. They checked her blood pressure and pulse and maybe did other tests during this time. Eventually the ambulance arrived and patient was very clear with everyone that she did not want to incur the expenses of riding in the ambulance and I offered to bring her wherever they suggested that she should go. They watched and evaluated her for a while and eventually had her sign the form declining the ambulance transportation. They suggested that she make an appointment with her doctor but did not suggest that we take patient to an emergency room. We departed and patient did not afterward seem to experience any symptoms from the vaccine other than some of the general feelings of being sick, soreness at the injection site, etc. that others report with the Moderna vaccine.

I received an allergy immunotherapy shot the day before my first dose of the vaccine and instantly felt nauseous and extremely tired after receiving the vaccine, which continued for two days after receiving tut. Three days later, I woke up struggling to breathe (but not anaphylactic), covered in hives, itchy all over, shaking, disoriented, and chilled but not truly feverish. I reported this to my allergist, who prescribed prednisone and suggested the vaccine combined with immunotherapy were too much for my immune system for one week. The hives, itchiness, and difficulty breathing lasted about four days. I struggled with fatigue and nausea for over two weeks, stopping all school and work in the meantime. After my second dose, I feel just a bit tired and sore, so I think this truly was a bad reaction to the two injections combined rather than to the vaccine itself. Still, it was a debilitating experience, and I would recommend considering putting out guidance that other immunotherapy patients space out their allergy injections and vaccines farther than I did.

This regulatory authority case was reported by a health care professional and describes the occurrence of CHOKING (Choked), SYNCOPE (Patient fainted) and SEIZURE (Began seizing for about 5 seconds) in a 21-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 007b21a) for COVID-19 vaccination. On 12-Apr-2021, the patient experienced CHOKING (Choked) (seriousness criterion medically significant), SYNCOPE (Patient fainted) (seriousness criterion medically significant), SEIZURE (Began seizing for about 5 seconds) (seriousness criterion medically significant), FOAMING AT MOUTH (She began foaming saliva), HYPOTONIA (hypotonia) and GAIT DISTURBANCE (Became limp). The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. The date of the second dose was 05/25/2021, which is when the side effects started. I had the normal and expected effects, such as a sore arm and fatigue. I began my period that morning, before I went in for the shot. I would like to be as detailed as possible, so I will likely include some graphic details in this description. My apologies in advance. My period normally lasts 3-4 days and is moderate (as far as I know) regarding blood loss. After the second dose, the flow was extremely heavy and my period lasted for almost an entire week (7 days). It was miserable. I was bloated and tender in that area, and extremely tired. I was also cramping, which is unusual for me nowadays. About two weeks after that, I felt a stabbing or ripping pain in the uterus area. It stayed for about two days, throbbing every minute or so. I could not sleep those days. It was not so unbearable that I could not perform everyday actions, but it was taking up a good portion of my thoughts that weekend. After that, it went away and I thought it was over. About three days ago from today (today is June 22nd, or 06/22/2021), the pain returned and I knew it meant the start of my period. The timing was normal. The next day I began bleeding, but the flow is again much heavier than normal. The pain is back and much worse than before. I am going through many more pads than usual and it is, for me, a worrying amount of blood. Since this is the second period in a row I am experiencing this, I felt it was necessary to report it in. I hope this is okay and not taking resources from those with worse issues. I would also like to note that I experienced my first panic attack in 5 years the night of my second dose (for no reason- they've always had a concrete reason for occurring) and my anxiety was notably worse that week (I am on medication and was otherwise doing very well managing the anxiety). During the attack I experienced the usual symptoms: my throat closing up and making it harder to breathe, and uncontrollable shaking and crying. I was not thinking of anything that would make me nervous at the time of the attack. I had just finished an online gaming session with a friend and was showering to prepare for bed, so I was fully relaxed. Additionally, my mental health has notably dipped a bit over the last month, though there are a number of factors at play and I don't want to blame the vaccine for that. However, I was told to at least make note of it here just in case there does end up being a correlation.

Anaphylactic reaction; Burning sensation in eyeballs; Wheezing; Rales; Airways were closing; Can't breathe; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 22-year-old, female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced an anaphylactic reaction, burning sensation in eyeballs/abnormal sensation in eye, wheezing, rales, airways were closing/obstructive airways disorder, and can't breathe/dyspnoea. The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 05 Feb 2021, within 5 minutes prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 011J20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 05 Feb 2021, within 5 minutes after receiving her second dose of vaccine, the patient reported a burning sensation in her eyeballs, followed by wheezing and rales in her lungs. She was given epinephrine and taken to the emergency room via an ambulance. She was given a second dose of epinephrine. Her airways were closing and she could not breathe. She was given a steroid, diphenhydramine, H2 antagonist and albuterol. Consent given for follow up calls. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The outcome of the events, anaphylactic reaction, burning sensation in eyeballs, wheezing, rales, airways were closing, and can't breathe, was not provided.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the onset date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

The patient was treated with EPINEPHRINE (EPIPEN) on 04-Jun-2021 for Anaphylactic shock, at a dose of 2 dosage form and DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE (BENADRYL [DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE]) on 04-Jun-2021 for Hives, at a dose of 25 milligram every six hours. Chest hurting; Breathing becomes painful; Tingling sensation on her tongue and says that it feels bigger than normal; Tingling sensation on her tongue and says that it feels bigger than normal; Feeling cold; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning a 23-year-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced chest hurting, breathing became painful, tingling tongue, tongue discomfort, feeling cold. The patient's medical history was not provided. No concomitant medications were provided. On 09 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot Number: 012L20A) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 09 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a tingling sensation on her tongue and felt that it was bigger than normal. She was given Diphenhydramine as an intervention. The patient started to feel cold. After 20 minutes, breathing became painful and her chest was hurting. The patient was given epinephrine and was transported to the hospital for continued monitoring. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of the events, chest hurting, breathing became painful, tingling tongue, tongue discomfort, feeling cold, was considered were not recovered/resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 23-year-old female patient who received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot 012L20A), and who experienced the serious unlisted events of Chest pain and Painful respiration and the non-serious unlisted events of tingling tongue, tongue discomfort, and feeling cold. Patient was treated with Benadryl and EpiPen prior to being transferred to hospital. Based on the current available information and temporal association between vaccination and the onset of events on the day of vaccination, a causal relationship cannot be excluded and the events are considered possibly related to the vaccine.

Close
Within 30 seconds of the injection of my second dose of Moderna, I experienced extreme nausea unlike any that I have experienced before. Within 1 minute of the injection, my face, arms, chest, and neck flushed and I turned completely red. I felt hot and started to sweat. At the same time, I began having trouble breathing with the sensation that my throat was beginning to close. My eyes filled with tears and I was not able to talk to communicate what was happening. My mom, who was with me at the time of vaccination, asked the administering pharmacist if I could remove my mask because I was having trouble breathing. Throughout this reaction, the pharmacist froze and was visibly in shock of what was happening. Because of this, my mom began asking me questions to figure out what else I was experiencing. Once I was able to remove the mask and breathe deeply, the reaction subsided after two minutes. The pharmacist, after my reaction began to subside, stated that they had an epipen ready to administer if needed. I was never administered the epipen. The pharmacist asked me to wait 30 minutes instead of the general 15 minutes before leaving the site. Because the symptoms went away and did not return within the 30 minutes, I left the site. After the vaccination, I experienced a low-grade fever for 79 hours, chills, a headache, muscle aches, and extreme fatigue. After realizing my reaction was not considered ?normal,? I began to research and realized these symptoms align with anaphylaxis, even though they subsided quickly after experiencing them.

Obese female patient with history of diabetes and seizure came to our pharmacy for second Moderna covid dose. A few minutes after receiving the vaccine, she was feeling lightheaded and nausea. I asked the patient to come back in to the consultation room where she could sit or lay down on the floor. The patient was able to walk back into the room with a little assistance from her mother. She sat on the floor for a bit, still breathing fine, and said she wanted to throw up. I grabbed a trash can, napkins, and a pedialyte bottle for her. She did not throw up but started breathing a little heavier and said she was about to faint. I got the epi pen ready and told her please lay down if she has to. At this point she fell to her right side and slightly hit her head against the wall. It appeared that she stopped breathing for few seconds, but I still felt a pulse on her wrist. It also appeared that she went into a seizure, her upper body stiffened up and her arms were slightly flailing. I immediately called 911 and about 1 minute later, both the mother and I could clearly see the patient breathing as indicative by the rising/lowering chest. I also felt a stronger pulse on her wrist. I did not inject the epi pen. Paramedics arrived shortly and after about 5-10 minutes of talking to her, the patient began to gain conscious but looked exhausted. They transported her to the hospital. Per the mother, patient was completely fine after the first dose of Moderna; also just had a seizure a few days before the second Moderna dose. The whole incident was about 20 minutes from administering the vaccine to paramedics transporting her away.

Everything was fine until the January 28th when I developed a large red lump during the day while at work that was severely itchy and hot. When I got home from work I had a low grade fever. She drew a purple circle around the area and told me that if it goes outside the marked area or I feel any new symptoms, to go to the emergency room. Saturday morning on the 30th i woke up to my entire arm red and hot. I felt like I had a huge sunburn. I couldn?t put my sweatshirt on because it was so hot. The emergency room doctor told me I was fine and to keep taking the antibiotics that were given to me yesterday from my primary care doctor. After the emergency room I went to work and started to feel dizzy and nauseous. My hands became sweaty but the rest of my body was cold. I started having a butterfly feeling in my chest. My Apple Watch alerted me that my heart rate was over 100 bpm. That night before bed I had another low grade fever. On Sunday the 31st I noticed the red area was gone but instead it was a dark purple. I felt okay Sunday besides a rapid pulse. Monday February 1st I woke up out of a dead sleep sweating, butterfly feeling in my chest and dizzy. I tried to take my pulse while laying down but it was so fast I couldn?t keep up with it. I called my primary doctors office and they were able to get me in that afternoon. All morning my pulse was spiking and then drastically dropping. My pulse and blood pressure was also fine. The doctor told me she believed all of the symptoms I had were from the medication I take at night (doxazosin-to relax my muscles and help with sleep.) She also told me she believed some of it was my mental health issues taking over. She told me the cellulitis looked fine and sent me home. February 2nd I woke up to a large red ring outside of the purple marker, numb finger tips and butterfly feeling in my chest. All day I received alerts that my pulse was falling and spiking. I sent my primary doctor an email and she told me she didn?t think it was cellulitis anymore, maybe a hematoma but she wasn?t sure. Since January 28th I still struggle everyday with the butterfly feeling in my chest, blurry vision, low grade temps, alerts of pulse, dizziness and breathing difficulties. When my pulse is very fast, I have a hard time talking, remembering what I was going to say and focusing. I?ve had multiple coworkers ask me if I?m okay because I?ll randomly stop talking and stare off and then I?m alerted that my pulse has either spiked or dropped drastically after spiking. My pulse is never consistent. It is always ranging from 57-155bpm. I realized at first I may have what they call ?COVID arm? but my symptoms haven?t gotten any better. No answers have been given to me or a diagnosis. The first diagnosis that they thought was cellulitis. Then it was ?in my head and behavioral.? Then it was a hematoma. Now it?s an ?I don?t know.? I have tried Benadryl for the itching, ice packs for the days that I?m swollen, Tylenol for the fevers and pain but I never have any relief.

Close
I had pain in my left arm, and within an hour or two I was pretty exhausted and out of it. I figured it would go away, it got worse the next day, and finally on Saturday when I woke up it was hard for me to breathe and I had pain/tightness in my chest. I went into the ER on Sunday morning and after a day of testing was diagnosed with: - Deep vein thrombosis of bilateral lower extremities - Pulmonary embolism, bilateral - DVT, bilateral lower limbs I had at least 5 clots in my legs and several more in my lungs but they said there was no way to know the full amount. I had been on HRT for over two and a half years and had no problems, then 4 days after I received my first shot I was informed that I had almost died several times due to the clots. When I explained to my doctor that I thought the clots were related to my shot he shrugged it off, said it was impossible, told it was just my hormones, and said that "Covid is no big deal and we're overexaggerating how bad it is compared to other things...". So I don't think any of this was reported. Later I saw a blood specialist who told me it was impossible for hormones to do this much damage in the span of a few days without something else effecting it, and told me to cancel my next shot even after we learned I had APS. All and all I would really appreciate someone looking into this to at least make sure there isn't something else going on, as the timing of this is was too close and I know Covid shots have had the rare chance of causing the exact kind of thing I went through.

The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included Mast cell activation syndrome. Concurrent medical conditions included Drug allergy (Novocain (all cains)allergy), Drug allergy (Singulair allergy), Drug allergy (Cromolyn sodium allergy), Postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome and Ehlers-Danlos syndrome. Concomitant products included IVABRADINE HYDROCHLORIDE (CORLANOR), RIVASTIGMINE (EXELON [RIVASTIGMINE]), BUPROPION HYDROCHLORIDE (WELLBUTRIN), KETOTIFEN, CETIRIZINE HYDROCHLORIDE (ZYRTEC [CETIRIZINE HYDROCHLORIDE]), FAMOTIDINE (PEPCID [FAMOTIDINE]), NALTREXONE, IMMUNOGLOBULINS NOS (IMMUNOGLOBULIN I.V) and DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE (BENADRYL [DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE]) for an unknown indication. On 30-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 08-May-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 08-May-2021, the patient experienced PAIN IN EXTREMITY (Arm soreness/progressed into shooting leg pain) and INAPPROPRIATE SCHEDULE OF PRODUCT ADMINISTRATION (2nd dose 08May2021 (delayed due to a sleep study due to sleep apnea). On 14-May-2021, the patient experienced DECREASED APPETITE (loss of appetite), WEIGHT DECREASED (lost 10 % of body weight), NAUSEA (Nausea) and FATIGUE (Fatigue). On 16-May-2021, the patient experienced MAST CELL ACTIVATION SYNDROME (severe mast cell reaction ( is a mast cell patient)). On 22-May-2021, the patient experienced ARTHRALGIA (large joint pain). On 26-May-2021, the patient experienced TACHYCARDIA (tachycardia spiked to 130,tachycardia continues) and DYSPNOEA (Shortness of breath). On 02-Jun-2021, the patient experienced TENDERNESS (Full body tenderness) and INFLUENZA LIKE ILLNESS (Flu like pain). On 08-Jun-2021, the patient experienced FEELING ABNORMAL (Adrenaline rushes), PAIN (Felt like an electric shot like pain), HOT FLUSH (hot flashes) and HEADACHE (Major headaches level 7 pain). On an unknown date, the patient experienced NEUROPATHY PERIPHERAL (severe neuropathy in feet) (seriousness criterion medically significant). an unknown date, the patient experienced GAIT INABILITY (Gait disruption,Couldn't walk more than 10 meters) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and SCIATICA (Radiating sciatic, bilateral). The patient was treated with KETOROLAC TROMETHAMINE (TORADOL) (intravenous) on 08-Jun-2021 for Headache, at a dose of 30 mg; DEXAMETHASONE (DECADRON [DEXAMETHASONE]) for Neuropathy, at an unspecified dose and frequency and GABAPENTIN for Neuropathy, at an unspecified dose and frequency. On 08-May-2021, INAPPROPRIATE SCHEDULE OF PRODUCT ADMINISTRATION (2nd dose 08May2021 (delayed due to a sleep study due to sleep apnea) had resolved. At the time of the report, NEUROPATHY PERIPHERAL (severe neuropathy in feet), MAST CELL ACTIVATION SYNDROME (severe mast cell reaction ( is a mast cell patient)), DYSPNOEA (Shortness of breath), FEELING ABNORMAL (Adrenaline rushes), DECREASED APPETITE (loss of appetite), WEIGHT DECREASED (lost 10 % of body weight), SCIATICA (Radiating sciatic, bilateral), TENDERNESS (Full body tenderness), INFLUENZA LIKE ILLNESS (Flu like pain), PAIN IN EXTREMITY (Arm soreness/progressed into shooting leg pain), PAIN (Felt like an electric shot like pain), HOT FLUSH (hot flashes), HEADACHE (Major headaches level 7 pain), ARTHRALGIA (large joint pain), NAUSEA (Nausea) and FATIGUE (Fatigue) outcome was unknown and GAIT INABILITY (Gait disruption,Couldn't walk more than 10 meters) and TACHYCARDIA (tachycardia spiked to 130,tachycardia continues) had not resolved. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 26-May-2021, Heart rate: 130 (High) tachycardia spiked to 130. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. Attendee received first dose Moderna vaccine at 15:15 in the right arm. Lot# 016C21A. At 15:28 voiced complaints of chest tightness and feeling like she was having hot flashes. 911 was called. Her skin was warm and dry. Her respirations were tachypneic. They brought the cot to her, but she did not want to lie down and so she leaned over the cot. 15:30  Vital signs taken. HR: 93 BP: 120/60 15:35  Benadryl 50 mg given via mouth. 15:36  Reported that she was becoming short of breath and itchy. 15:38  EMS arrived and took over care of the attendee. She was taken away via ambulance to the emergency room.

Within just a few minutes of receiving my first dose, I begant to feel nauseous. I sat down and began to have trouble breathing. My vision became splotchy and my ears plugged up. My chest began to hurt and my trouble breathing became worse, to the point of gasping for air. I was sweating a lot despite being indoors. This lasted about 10 minutes.

4:00pm- Received vaccine (Moderna dose 1) 4:10pm- Started experiencing throat swelling, trouble breathing, increased anxiety. Alerted pharmacist that I was having a reaction and they have me a bottle of water. 4:25-4:30pm- Alerted pharmacist again that the reaction was still going on and I was given a 25mg Benadryl. It was hard to swallow but I was still able to take it. 4:30pm-5:30pm- Waited to see if the Benadryl would help but it did not. Had to call a family member to take me to ER. 6pm-8pm - Went to ER to get checked out. Doctor said I was having an allergic reaction (similar to a shellfish reaction) and was given IV steroid (Dexmethosone) and some fluids.
